parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake System Failure (Vacuum Pump, Brake Booster, and Hose Issues)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: brake pedal travels to the floorboard
abnormal amount of pressure required to stop the vehicle
inability to slow or stop the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Bridgestone Potenza RE050A Tire Sidewall Separation/Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The separation or failure of the tire sidewall can lead to a loss of tire pressure, causing the vehicle to lose control, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Blisters or bubbles on the tire sidewall

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the passenger seat mat sensor can cause the airbag and seatbelt warning lights to illuminate, indicating a fault in the passenger restraint system, which can lead to the airbag not deploying in the event of an accident, potentially causing injury or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag and seatbelt warning lights illuminate
the passenger airbag may not deploy
the "Pass. Restraint System - Fault" warning message appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to stalling, engine damage, and potentially a crash.
symptoms: the vehicle's air conditioning is not cold.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake vacuum pump can cause brake failure, leading to a loss of control and potentially a crash.
symptoms: Engine oil leaks below the brake vacuum pump

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag system can cause the airbags to deploy unexpectedly or not deploy in the event of a crash, leading to injuries or fatalities.
Engine backfiring can cause a loss of power, stalling, and potentially a crash.
